'''Coniology''' or '''koniology''' (from [[Ancient Greek|Greek]] {{lang|grc|[[wiktionary:κόνις|κόνις]]}}, ''konis'' or {{lang|grc|[[wiktionary:κονία|κονίᾱ]]}}, ''koniā'', "dust"; and {{lang|grc|[[wiktionary:-λογία|-λογία]]}}, ''[[wiktionary:-logia|-logia]]'') is the study of atmospheric [[dust]] and its effects. Samples of dust are often collected by a device called [[coniometer]].

