'''Vitrophyre''' is a [[volcanic rock]] with a [[porphyritic]] texture in which larger crystals ([[phenocrysts]]) are embedded in a glassy [[groundmass]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theodora.com/geology/glossaryuv.html |title=Vitrophyre definition from the Dictionary of Geology |work= |accessdate=2010-05-17}}.</ref>

